<PageTitle>Trucking Step 4: Event Binding - Example</PageTitle>

<div class="min-h-screen py-8 rounded-4xl bg-gray-50">
    <div class="w-full mx-auto px-4 max-w-5xl">
        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="mb-8">
            <a href="/trucking-guide"
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm sm:text-base text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 mb-4">
                <span>‚Üê</span> Back to Trucking Guide
            </a>
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                üéØ Step 4: Event Binding
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
                Handle user interactions with event binding, update component state, and trigger UI re-renders
                automatically.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- What You'll Learn (Gradient Banner) -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-gray-100 to-blue-100 rounded-2xl p-5 sm:p-6 mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">What You'll Learn</h2>

            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 text-sm sm:text-base">
                Event binding is how your Blazor components respond to user interactions like clicks, form inputs, and
                keyboard events. Blazor's reactive system automatically re-renders the UI when component state changes,
                making it easy to build interactive applications without manual DOM manipulation.
            </p>

            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-sm sm:text-base text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                <li>Use @@onclick to bind button click events to C# methods</li>
                <li>Update component state with simple variable assignments - Blazor handles the rest</li>
                <li>Write synchronous handlers with <code>private void</code> for simple operations</li>
                <li>Write asynchronous handlers with <code>private async Task</code> for API calls or delays</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="mt-2 pt-3 border-t border-blue-200">
                <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">
                    <strong>üí° Key Concepts:</strong> @@onclick, State Management, Event Handlers, Automatic
                    Re-rendering
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
                    <span class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-gray-600">‚Üí Related tips:</span>
                    <a href="/tips#onclick"
                        class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full text-[11px] sm:text-xs font-medium hover:bg-blue-200 transition-colors">@@onclick</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Sample Component (White Card) -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200 mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">üß© Sample Component: Counter</h2>

            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">
                This component demonstrates event binding with a simple counter that responds to button clicks.
            </p>

            <!-- Full code example -->
            <div class="bg-gray-100 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4">
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Counter.razor</div>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mb-2">A complete counter component showing event binding with @@onclick
                    and state management.</p>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-4 mb-3 text-[11px] text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                    <li>@@onclick binds button clicks to C# methods (Increment, Decrement, Reset)</li>
                    <li>currentCount is component state that triggers UI updates when changed</li>
                    <li>Methods are simple void functions - no async needed for basic operations</li>
                    <li>Blazor automatically re-renders when currentCount changes</li>
                </ul>
                <pre data-code-title="Razor + C# (Counter.razor)"
                    class="code-block text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono text-gray-800 w-full max-w-full overflow-x-auto">@@page "/counter"

&lt;div class="min-h-screen py-8 bg-gray-50"&gt;
    &lt;div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4"&gt;
        &lt;h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6"&gt;Counter&lt;/h1&gt;
        
        &lt;div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 p-6"&gt;
            &lt;div class="text-center mb-6"&gt;
                &lt;p class="text-sm text-gray-500"&gt;Current count&lt;/p&gt;
                &lt;p class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900"&gt;@@currentCount&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3"&gt;
                &lt;button class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full border border-gray-200 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50"
                        @@onclick="Decrement"&gt;-1&lt;/button&gt;
                &lt;button class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-white bg-gray-900 hover:opacity-90"
                        @@onclick="Increment"&gt;+1&lt;/button&gt;
                &lt;button class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full border border-gray-200 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50"
                        @@onclick="Reset"&gt;Reset&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

@@code {
    private int currentCount = 0;
  
    private void Increment()
    {
        currentCount++;
    }
  
    private void Decrement()
    {
        currentCount--;
    }
  
    private void Reset()
    {
        currentCount = 0;
    }
}</pre>
            </div>

            <!-- Step-by-step breakdown -->
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Step-by-step breakdown</h3>
            <div class="grid gap-4">
                <div class="bg-gray-100 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                    <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">1. Component state</div>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mb-2">The currentCount variable holds the counter's value and
                        triggers re-renders when modified.</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 mb-2 text-[11px] text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                        <li>Declared as private field in @@code block</li>
                        <li>Initialized to 0</li>
                        <li>Referenced in markup with @@currentCount</li>
                    </ul>
                    <pre
                        class="code-block text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono text-gray-800 w-full max-w-full overflow-x-auto">private int currentCount = 0;</pre>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gray-100 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                    <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">2. Event binding with @@onclick</div>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mb-2">Buttons use @@onclick to call methods when clicked.</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 mb-2 text-[11px] text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                        <li>@@onclick="Increment" calls the Increment method</li>
                        <li>Method name without parentheses (not Increment())</li>
                        <li>Blazor automatically wires up the event handler</li>
                    </ul>
                    <pre
                        class="code-block text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono text-gray-800 w-full max-w-full overflow-x-auto">&lt;button @@onclick="Increment"&gt;+1&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button @@onclick="Decrement"&gt;-1&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button @@onclick="Reset"&gt;Reset&lt;/button&gt;</pre>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-gray-100 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                    <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">3. Event handler methods</div>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mb-2">Simple void methods that modify state when called.</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc ml-4 mb-2 text-[11px] text-gray-600 space-y-1">
                        <li>Increment adds 1 to currentCount</li>
                        <li>Decrement subtracts 1 from currentCount</li>
                        <li>Reset sets currentCount back to 0</li>
                        <li>All trigger automatic UI updates</li>
                    </ul>
                    <pre
                        class="code-block text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono text-gray-800 w-full max-w-full overflow-x-auto">private void Increment() { currentCount++; }
private void Decrement() { currentCount--; }
private void Reset() { currentCount = 0; }</pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Live Demo -->
        <div class="bg-black/3 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">üé¨ Live Demo</h2>

            <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
                <div class="text-center mb-6">
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Current count</p>
                    <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">@currentCount</p>
                </div>

                <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3">
                    <button class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full border border-gray-200 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50"
                        @onclick="Decrement">-1</button>
                    <button class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-white bg-gray-900 hover:opacity-90"
                        @onclick="Increment">+1</button>
                    <button class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full border border-gray-200 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50"
                        @onclick="Reset">Reset</button>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-4 text-center">üí° Click buttons to see state changes in real-time!</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Important Notes & Tips (White Card) -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200 mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">üìù Important Notes & Tips</h2>

            <div class="space-y-3">
                <!-- Pro Tips (Blue) -->
                <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                    <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-blue-900 mb-3">üí° Pro Tips</h3>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div>
                            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-1">Use void for synchronous handlers</p>
                            <p class="text-xs text-blue-800">Simple state updates don't need async. Use
                                <code>private void MethodName()</code> for cleaner code.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-1">Use async Task for API calls</p>
                            <p class="text-xs text-blue-800">When your handler needs to await (HTTP requests, delays,
                                database calls), use <code>private async Task MethodName()</code>.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-1">No manual DOM updates needed</p>
                            <p class="text-xs text-blue-800">Unlike JavaScript frameworks, you don't call setState() or
                                update the DOM. Just change the variable - Blazor handles the rest.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Troubleshooting (Yellow) -->
                <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                    <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-yellow-900 mb-2">‚ö†Ô∏è Troubleshooting</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-sm text-yellow-900 space-y-1">
                        <li><strong>Method not found?</strong> Ensure the method is defined in the @@code block and
                            spelled correctly.</li>
                        <li><strong>Async void warning?</strong> Use <code>async Task</code> instead of
                            <code>async void</code> for proper error handling.</li>
                        <li><strong>UI not updating?</strong> Make sure you're modifying a component field, not a local
                            variable inside the method.</li>
                        <li><strong>Build error with @@onclick?</strong> Use method name without parentheses:
                            <code>@@onclick="Method"</code> not <code>@@onclick="Method()"</code>.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- How to do it (Gradient Banner) -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-gray-100 to-blue-100 rounded-2xl p-5 sm:p-6 mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">üõ†Ô∏è How to do it</h2>
            <ol class="list-decimal ml-5 space-y-2 text-gray-700 text-sm sm:text-base">
                <li>
                    <strong>Create Counter.razor:</strong>
                    Create a new file at <code>Components/Pages/Counter.razor</code>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Copy the sample code:</strong>
                    Use the complete Counter.razor code from the example above
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Run your application:</strong>
                    Execute <code>dotnet run</code> and navigate to <code>http://localhost:5000/counter</code>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Test event binding:</strong>
                    Click the +1, -1, and Reset buttons to see state changes in real-time
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- Mark Complete Section (Green Card) -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border-2 border-green-200 mb-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between gap-4">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Finished Step 4?</h3>
